data.chText: 死去了的；已死的；亡故的

data.enText: a person who has died, especially recently

ex.enText: The dead tree was cut down.

ex.chText: 他的尸体安静地躺在床上。
ex.enText: His dead body lay peacefully on the bed.

synonyms.bx: 普通用词，指人和物失去生命的。

ex.chText: 死者给他的孙子留下一大笔钱。
ex.enText: The deceased left a large sum of money to his grandson.

synonyms.bx: 法律术语，指人已死亡的；常用作 the deceased, 尤指新近去世的人。

ex.chText: 遵照已故父亲的遗嘱，他有权接管所有的企业。
ex.enText: Following his late father's will, he was given the right to take over all  businesses.

ex.chText: 已故庄园主叫比尔·布朗。
ex.enText: The late master of the estate was named Bill Brown.

synonyms.bx: 只作定语，只用于人而不用于物。

tr: someone who is no longer alive
example: I wonder what the dead person would have done

value.def: The deceased is used to refer to a particular person or to particular people who have recently died.

example.ex: The identities of the deceased have now been determined.
example.tran: 死者的身份现在已经确定。

value.def: A deceased person is one who has recently died.
